column1: This file contains the S&P 500 straddle returns used in the paper 'Risk Premia and the VIX Term Structure' by Travis Johnson
The dates are in YYYYMMDD format
r_K^{straddle} gives the daily return of a long constant-maturity at the money straddle strategy with target maturity K months
r_K^{short straddle} gives the daily return of a short straddle strategy assuming a margin requirement equal to 20% of the current S&P 500 index level
